name: NPR
text:
Most of the federal contracts with companies involved in the crash program to make COVID-19 vaccines haven't been made public. 

But on Friday, HHS released its August contract with Moderna.

It's 53-pages long. Only 14 of them are free of redactions. https://t.co/Wbu8kZkDhk

name: NPR
text:
The value of the contract, for example, is blacked out with a note that it isn't disclosable under public records law because it's a trade secret.

"There's no question that that is not confidential," a lawyer says. "HHS was less transparent than Moderna." https://t.co/UhWWQmW8LM
